      • getMaxVelocity

        public double getMaxVelocity()
        This returns the max velocity the robot can achieve.
        This value can also be found using the Motion Log Viewer using a org.waltonrobotics.motion that is long and straight and has a high max velocity. or it can be calculated by using the (1 - kK)/ kV equation
        Returns:
        the max velocity the robot can achieve.

      • getKV

        public abstract double getKV()
        The velocity constant. This is the feed forward multiplier. Using the MotionLogger, KV is correct if lag error levels out.
        Returns:
        KV

      • getKAcc

        public abstract double getKAcc()
        The acceleration constant. This adds to the feed forward by giving a slight boost while accelerating or decelerating. Make this a very small number greater than 0 if anything.
        Returns:
        KAcc

      • getKK

        public abstract double getKK()
        This constant gives a slight boost to the motors. Make this a very small number greater than 0 if anything.
        Returns:
        KK

      • getKS

        public abstract double getKS()
        This is the constant for steering control. Using the MotionLogger, KS is correct when the cross track error provides a steady oscillation. Set this before KAng.
        Returns:
        KS

      • getKAng

        public abstract double getKAng()
        This is the constant for angle control. Using the MotionLogger, KT is correct when the angle and cross track errors approach 0.
        Returns:
        KAng

      • getKL

        public abstract double getKL()
        This is the lag constant. Using the MotionLogger, KL is correct when the lag error is (close to) 0.
        Returns:
        KL
